Orlando pirates FC announced on Tuesday that they have parted ways with their defender Patrick Phungwayo. The club has not elaborated or given details of the contract termination, however, announced that their separation with the player was on a mutual basis. Orlando Pirates Football Club has parted ways with Phungwayo. An agreement has been reached for the mutual termination of the contract following a meeting between both parties yesterday, the club said in a statement. The news follows earlier reports speculating that the defender was heading for an exit from the Buccaneers. The player was reportedly stripped off his jersey number which was given to latest signing Thamsanqa Sangweni. However, the Buccaneers extended their gratitude to the player. The Club would like to thank Mr Phungwayo for his service and wish him the best of luck in his future endeavours.&#8221; -TNA Reporter 